paragraph.content:
an officer of the Correctional Services Department or other person employed
                    in the prisons is found guilty of or pleads guilty to any criminal offence;
                    or

the summary dismissal of any officer of the Correctional Services Department or
                other person employed in the prisons in accordance with the Public Service
                (Administration) Order and government regulations;

all sums resulting from or donated in
                    connexion
                    with public entertainment performed by prisoners;

all sums received at any function organized to raise money for the fund
                    less any expenses which defray any necessary costs and charges in respect of
                    that function;

moneys confiscated by the Superintendent under rule 23 of the
                    Prison Rules (Cap. 234 sub. leg. A) and sums
                    derived from the sale of articles confiscated under that rule;

section.def:
acquire
                (取得) means acquire by purchase or by any other
            lawful means;

paragraph.content:
facilities that are not chargeable to the general revenue, including
                    holiday premises and recreational facilities (whether provided free or for a
                    charge);

social, educational and recreational activities and performances (whether
                    provided free or for a charge and whether provided for participation or as
                    spectator events);

section.def:
corporation
                (法團) means the corporation sole constituted under
                section 24D(1);

paragraph.content:
whose contract of service as an officer or employee of the Department has
                    expired on or after the person reached 55 years of age without the contract
                    being renewed;

section.def:
function
                (職能) includes a power, an authority and a
            duty;

Fund
                (基金) means the Correctional Services Department
            Welfare Fund continued by section 24E;

paragraph.content:
all fees collected from social, educational and recreational activities
                organized by or on behalf of the Commissioner for the purposes of the
                Fund;

providing and maintaining amenities for the use and enjoyment of
                    Correctional Services employees and former Correctional Services
                    employees;
